felt threatened due to something or
someone or have you felt that something
is going to harm you the word jeopardize
basically means to be in a situation or
to put someone into a situation which is
dangerous and harmful it also means to
take a risk that may prove to be
dangerous which in turn can endanger
your position to jeopardize a situation
or an activity means to do something
that may lead to destruction or failure
when something is at stake it means it
is jeopardized
for example drunk drivers always
jeopardize the lives of others as their
irrational driving can lead to fatal
accidents endangering innocent lives as
the word jeopardize shows the action of
threatening or harming someone it is a
verb okay now that you know what
jeopardise means let's take a look at
some example sentences to see how you
can use it in your daily conversation
example 1 to make big bucks quickly the
stuntman jeopardized his life by
performing deadly stunts in the film
example two John worked extremely hard
for his medical entrance examination as
failure in this exam could jeopardize
his whole future example three experts
say the drastic reduction in the white

future survival example for Mary has
lost her glow and charm and looks very

Susie told Jenny
